						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Jīvaraksha Timmana,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Mācherla Chenna</hi> erected a tower at the place where <hi rend="bold">Chīlama-Nāyiḍu</hi> planted (?) his spear. Contains some human figures bearing the names of <hi rend="bold">Pina-Malidēvarāja, Tomalidēvarāja, Chīlama-Nāyiḍu, Peda-Malidēvarāja,</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Rākshati • • .</hi></p>						

